{"title":"vêtements/clothes","markdown":{"yaml":{"title":"vêtements/clothes","author":"Kunal Khurana","date":"01-31-2025","categories":["A1/A2","vêtements","clothes"],"image":"vetements.png"},"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n\n<div style=\"text-align: left; padding: 10px;\">\n  <a href=\"mailto:info@frenchwithkunal.ca\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"margin: 0 10px; color: #000;\"><i class=\"fas fa-envelope fa-lg\"></i></a>\n  <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/frenchwithkunal\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"margin: 0 10px; color: #E1306C;\"><i class=\"fab fa-instagram fa-lg\"></i></a>\n  <a href=\"https://frenchwithkunal.ca\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"margin: 0 10px; color: #0077b5;\"><i class=\"fas fa-globe fa-lg\"></i></a>\n  <a href=\"https://whatsapp.com/channel/0029Vb57n2e7dmegpjYpyi3V\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"margin: 0 10px; color: #25D366;\"><i class=\"fab fa-whatsapp fa-lg\"></i></a>\n  <button onclick=\"copyLink()\" style=\"background-color: #0077b5; color: white; padding: 8px 16px; border: none; border-radius: 4px; cursor: pointer; margin-left: 10px;\">\n    <i class=\"fas fa-copy\"></i> \n  </button>\n  <span id=\"copy-message\" style=\"margin-left: 10px; color: green; display: none;\">Link copied!</span>\n</div>\n\n<script>\n  function copyLink() {\n    // Get the current page URL\n    const url = window.location.href;\n    \n    // Copy the URL to the clipboard\n    navigator.clipboard.writeText(url).then(() => {\n      // Show a confirmation message\n      const message = document.getElementById(\"copy-message\");\n      message.style.display = \"inline\";\n      setTimeout(() => {\n        message.style.display = \"none\";\n      }, 2000); // Hide the message after 2 seconds\n    });\n  }\n</script>\n\n\n\n::: {.content-visible when-profile=\"english\"}\nIn one of my [recent lessons](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1vqKMtqE6OtIyDmkKraVv77rR2gZF_pdk/view?usp=drive_link), I taught my students how to ask for [clothes](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1vqKMtqE6OtIyDmkKraVv77rR2gZF_pdk/view?usp=drive_link) in French, a practical skill for any language learner. For example, you can say: \"Hello, I'm looking for a \\[sweater/dress/shirt\\] in size \\[M, L, etc.\\]. Do you have this model in \\[color\\]?\" Or: \"Do you have these jeans in another size?\"\n\nThese simple phrases make it easy to navigate a store or shop online in French. I also explained the importance of using polite terms like \"please\" (s'il vous plaît) and \"thank you\" (merci). My students loved practicing these expressions, and some even created dialogues to practice!\n\nWhat about you? Have you ever tried shopping for clothes in French? Share your experiences in the comments!\n:::\n\n::: {.content-visible when-profile=\"french\"}\nDans une de mes [leçons récentes](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1vqKMtqE6OtIyDmkKraVv77rR2gZF_pdk/view?usp=drive_link), j'ai enseigné à mes élèves comment demander des [vêtements](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1vqKMtqE6OtIyDmkKraVv77rR2gZF_pdk/view?usp=drive_link) en français, une compétence pratique pour tout apprenant de la langue. Par exemple, on peut dire : \"Bonjour, je cherche un \\[pull/robe/chemise\\] en taille \\[M, L, etc.\\]. Avez-vous ce modèle en \\[couleur\\] ?\" Ou encore : \"Est-ce que vous avez ce jean dans une autre taille?\"\n\nCes phrases simples permettent de naviguer dans un magasin ou de faire des achats en ligne en français. J'ai aussi expliqué l'importance d'utiliser des termes comme \"s'il vous plaît\" et \"merci\" pour rester poli. Mes élèves ont adoré pratiquer ces expressions, et certains ont même imaginé des dialogues pour s'entraîner!\n:::","srcMarkdownNoYaml":"\n\n\n<div style=\"text-align: left; padding: 10px;\">\n  <a href=\"mailto:info@frenchwithkunal.ca\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"margin: 0 10px; color: #000;\"><i class=\"fas fa-envelope fa-lg\"></i></a>\n  <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/frenchwithkunal\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"margin: 0 10px; color: #E1306C;\"><i class=\"fa